{
  "title": "ISic000568. I.Sicily inscription 000568",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" style=\"left: -4em;\">Col. 1<br></span>  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Marcus · Sicribonius\n                    Marci  libertus ·\n                    Stymphalus\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Marcus\">M(arcus)</span> · <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Sicribonius\">S{i}cribonius</span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Marci\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"libertinatio\" data-text=\"Marci\">M(arci)</span></span> l(ibertus) · <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Stymphalus\">Stymphalus</span></span>  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" style=\"left: -4em;\">Col. 2<br></span>  <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Caecilia\n                    \n                    Attica\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Caecilia\">Caecilia</span>  <br id=\"al5-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">..</span>  <br id=\"al6-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">6</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Attica\">Attica</span></span> · </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><span class=\"textpartnumber\" style=\"left: -4em;\">Col. 1<br></span><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Marcus · Sicribonius\n                    Marci  libertus ·\n                    Stymphalus\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Marcus\">M</span>·<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Sicribonius\">SICRIBONIUS</span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Marci\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"libertinatio\" data-text=\"Marci\">M</span></span>L·<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Stymphalus\">STYMPHALUS</span></span><span class=\"textpartnumber\" style=\"left: -4em;\">Col. 2<br></span><br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Caecilia\n                    \n                    Attica\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Caecilia\">CAECILIA</span><br id=\"al5-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··</span><br id=\"al6-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">6</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Attica\">ATTICA</span></span>·</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text of Salinas; note that Gualtherus (followed by Mommsen) recorded in single column, separating the two sections with a space, rather than in two columns</span></span>; </li><li><span class=\"1\">1: <span>Gualtherus: SICRIBONIVS, rightly, as per lapidem (and not SICIRIBONIVS as attributed to him by Mommsen).</span></span><br></li><li><span class=\"5\">5: <span>Gualtherus, Mommsen: vacat; Salinas notes that traces suggest something like 'M.L.'</span></span><br></li><li><span class=\"6\">6: <span>Gualtherus appears to print a large F to the right of the line, resolved by Mommsen as 'F(ecit)'; Salinas (rightly) suggests this is a typographer's addition, for the next page.</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou</a></p>  <p>Marcus Scribonius Stymphalus, freedman of Marcus. Caecilia Attica.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Mommsen was constrained to follow Gualtherus' report (second edition only), as Salinas' rediscovery of the piece came too late. The piece is not mentioned in I.L.Palermo and so is seemingly no longer in the museum.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> VIII 697 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002649\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002649</a></li><li> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 238 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931</a>  </li><li> Mommsen 1883 <a href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/CILv10pII1883\" target=\"_blank\">7318</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589</a></li><li> Salinas NSA 1883 567 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
  "divs": [
    {
