      "html": "<h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text of Salinas; note that Gualtherus (followed by Mommsen) recorded in single column, separating the two sections with a space, rather than in two columns</span></span>; </li><li><span class=\"1\">1: <span>Gualtherus: SICRIBONIVS, rightly, as per lapidem (and not SICIRIBONIVS as attributed to him by Mommsen).</span></span><br></li><li><span class=\"5\">5: <span>Gualtherus, Mommsen: vacat; Salinas notes that traces suggest something like 'M.L.'</span></span><br></li><li><span class=\"6\">6: <span>Gualtherus appears to print a large F to the right of the line, resolved by Mommsen as 'F(ecit)'; Salinas (rightly) suggests this is a typographer's addition, for the next page.</span></span></li></ul>"
